Program: The Documentary
Title: Episode 2 - Mexico
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00fc7vd
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 28 Mar 2011
Far from being in decline, as western newspaper headlines suggest, the nuclear family is emerging as the successful model across much of the developing world. Sociologists say it's now taking root in all but a handful of countries. But what makes it such an irresistable model for the 21st Century?